    • Constructor Detail

      • FoodNormal

        public FoodNormal​(Handler handler,
                  float x,
                  float y)
        Constructor of FoodNormal class only calls constructor of the abstract Food class with score set to 1. It takes the game handler for having access to the game map and its elements, an x-coordinate and a y-coordinate, which are both absolute in pixels, rather than in map tiles.

        It also sets local variables, and the bounding rectangle.

        Parameters:
        handler - game handler for accessing other elements of the game
        x - absolute x-coordinate in pixels
        y - absolute y-coordinate in pixels

    • Method Detail

      • setActive

        public void setActive​(boolean active)
        Sets active status of the food. If the food becomes inactive (it is eaten by PacMan), its score is added to player's score. If this was the last remaining normal food in the maze, level up.
        Overrides:
        setActive in class Food
        Parameters:
        active - new active status
